<LP>
   MOVIES: New Line Cinema Corp. plans to sell 600,000 newly
issued common shares to clients of Capital Research &amp;
Management Co. and Capital Guardian Trust Co., both units of
Capital Group Inc. The estimated $6 million investment would
give the investors a 7.9% stake in New Line and boost New
Line's shares outstanding to about 7.6 million. New Line will
use the money to fund film production.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   PUBLISHING: Maxwell Communication Corp.'s Macmillan Inc.
unit acquired Thorndike, a Unity, Maine, publisher of
large-print editions of current fiction and nonfiction books,
for $5.2 million.
